If there was ever a time to reminisce on seasons past 🥶 Anyone else walk outside and instantly question their decision to live here?? What keeps you in Chicago? 

For us, it’s all about the vibes. The spirit of the people in Chicago and the energy they bring to the city are unmatched. Not to mention Summertime Chi is so seductive 😮‍💨 stay warm & strong fam, let the thoughts of sunny rides down Lake Shore Dr, hitting the beach & blunt with friends, and letting that queer joy glow in the sunshine carry you through as you hold fam close for the winter. 🤗

Happy Holidays from the smallWORLD fam‼️ This time of year brings up lots of nuances in feelings for folks; just a reminder to be gentle with yourself whether you’re celebrating or not. 

It’s ok to crave the familiar connections and traditions with family. It’s also ok to guard your energy and protect your peace. You don’t owe anyone an explanation of your queerness or any other aspect of your identity! 

The family we’re born into wont always be the ones to understanding & uplift us. Queer folks have always reclaimed their power by building families out of community, surrounding ourselves with people who make us feel seen, loved and accepted, not just tolerated. 

Wishing you all the best vibes and the space to build new traditions, alone, or with family. You deserve peace and abundance.

✨WE LOVE YOU✨

One of our favorite parts of creating intentional space for queer folks is seeing the connections that are built within them. It makes it all worth it- we absolutely love to hear the love stories that have blossomed from smallWORLD spaces, and to see the friendships & chosen families that grow as well! There aren’t enough places for us to show up as our full selves, see our reflections in one another, and commune with folks who resonate with our struggles and can help us explore our freedom ✨ those relationships and connections are part of our purpose and we cherish the stories you share with us!

Tag a bestie or bae that you’ve connected with through smallWORLD! 🤩

A lot of y’all have been asking what we’re getting into for NYE 🪩 we won’t be throwing an event of our own, but we’re bringing in the new year in glitter & gold with the fam ✨ Saturday we’re partying with @bodyconfidenceforqueens, the city’s hottest movement artists & a$$ shakers 💃🏾 with vibes set by smallWORLD sound curators @tori_the_creator7 & @khalimelon. You don’t wanna miss the burlesque performances 🙌🏾 hit the link in BCQ bio to grab tickets and dance into 2023!

It’s been a hell of a year 🥵 The congregation has grown, but the mission is the same 💯 we’re here to advocate for Black queer joy baby! From the healing & eye opening convos that take place during Polyam Chats, to the freedom we explore through movement & music on the dance floor, the time we’ve shared this year is sacred. Seeking out our desires, living boldly out loud & creating intentional space for y’all to do the same is an incredible journey, learning and growing along the way, & shifting the culture as we go. 

The memories we create together are unmatched & we love y’all for the ENERGY you contribute 🫶🏾 we’re so excited for everything to come in 2023 ✨

Hoping you stepped into the New Year with the BADDEST b!tch energy❗️✨ Themes for the year include growth, exploring ourselves and our desires always, creating more space for joy & adventure, getting to the money & staying FNF. What are your goals?

Next Thursday we’re back on the couch for a virtual chat with your favorite polyam fam! 

Polyam Chats are an intentional and intimate space for casual discussions on non-monogamy and other related topics on life and love. Whether you’re single, partnered, polyamorous, or still figuring out if monogamy works for you, join this conversational space to break down expectations and gain perspective on what it means to build commitment and explore our desires. 

Grab your tickets now at the link in bio!

Happy Black History Month fam 🫶🏾 you know this celebration is/should be a year round thing, but why not take a lil extra time to be intentional about it?

We are our ancestors wildest dreams. As Black queer folks, the intersection of that identity makes it even more true. The way smallWORLD curates opportunities for us to take up space as our authentic selves is truly history in the making. These pics of y’all WILL be in history books 🙌🏾 From events designed for us to physically shake off our oppression and indulge our desires on the dance floor, to conversational spaces to verbally express them, and providing platforms for Black queer & trans artists & entrepreneurs- this isn’t easy work but it’s worth it. 

….We also deserve reparations 💸 Pay Black folks. Pay Black queer and trans artists. Pay our space makers! We can’t wait to have a space of our own soon where community can consistently find that intentional place to commune. In the meantime, we’re always taking donations for the cause.

Who is TORi? Just a week after ending my very public “couple goals” relationship, I delved into my vulnerabilities, baring both body and soul. Growing up as a Black non-binary individual, the world often felt like it was in shades of gray. My shyness, a shield I wore due to past traumas, kept me hidden, my voice a mere whisper. 

With the help of a good friend, I had a realization when they asked, 'What are 5 things you really love about yourself?'"When I thought about it, everything that came to mind was rooted in survival. Strength, Resilience, Adaptability.

I  want the community to know and see ME. **I want the world to know drives me to do what I do**. Part of my healing journey is acknowledging that it’s unnecessary to over explain myself. I initially had long paragraphs essentially all about my trauma. I am NOT my trauma!

I am a nerd who LOVES cats. I’m curious and I love to learn, and enjoy sharing all the knowledge I gain. Because Fuck gatekeeping! I have a passion for creating, whether it be DJing, jewelry, graphic design, photography, or most importantly intentional spaces. 

Before college, I never went to a single school dance and had few friends. I didn't realize it at the time, but smallWORLD has been my dream and destiny since 2014. I wanted to create something to share my passions and for all those kindred, silenced souls. 

This Sunday, come and meet TORi! Experience me in my truest, unrestricted form in a space curated EXCLUSIVELY by yours truly!
